00:16:00.140 --> 00:16:03.990
a reflection on the work you did
during the civil rights movement,

00:16:03.990 --> 00:16:09.250
and it ends more to come here.

00:16:09.250 --> 00:16:12.320
Are we in a period
now where we're seeing

00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:15.360
that there's more work
to be done here?

00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:17.040
&gt;&gt; Rep. John Lewis:
Well, I think we are.

00:16:17.040 --> 00:16:25.820
I just left an unbelievable meeting
when I go enter in on a discussion

00:16:25.820 --> 00:16:31.240
about it, but I think in America
today right now people are saying

00:16:31.240 --> 00:16:34.410
where are we going as a
nation and as a people?

00:16:34.410 --> 00:16:35.710
Are we going backward?

00:16:35.710 --> 00:16:37.470
Are we going to stand still?

00:16:37.470 --> 00:16:39.250
Or are we going to go forward?

00:16:39.250 --> 00:16:45.230
I think [inaudible] tell us
all that we've come a distance,

00:16:45.230 --> 00:16:49.930
we've made a lot of progress,
but there are forces that want

00:16:49.930 --> 00:16:56.290
to slow us down or take us back,
and we would like for people

00:16:56.290 --> 00:17:02.120 position:56%
to be hopeful, to be optimistic, and
to understand that we're one people,

00:17:02.120 --> 00:17:06.170
that it doesn't matter whether
we're black or white, Latino,

00:17:06.170 --> 00:17:09.830
Asian American, or Native American.

00:17:09.830 --> 00:17:12.860
We all live in the same house.

00:17:12.860 --> 00:17:16.160
Not just American house,
but the world house.

00:17:16.160 --> 00:17:19.380
There was a man by the name of
A. Philip Randolph that we speak

00:17:19.380 --> 00:17:25.190
about because he was the man
who called together the march

00:17:25.190 --> 00:17:28.600
on Washington, and he used
to say from time to time,

00:17:28.600 --> 00:17:32.650
maybe our foremothers and
our forefathers all came

00:17:32.650 --> 00:17:36.000
to this great land
in different ships,

00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:37.350
but we're all in the same boat now.

00:17:37.350 --> 00:17:41.570
We have to look out for each
other and care for each other.

00:17:41.570 --> 00:17:47.000
And Dr. King said on one occasion,
and he said it so beautifully,

00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:55.080
that we must learn to live together
as one family, as one people.

00:17:55.080 --> 00:17:58.860
If not, [inaudible] as fools.

00:17:58.860 --> 00:18:08.700
And I think this is message that
we try to convey in "March."

00:18:08.700 --> 00:18:11.190
That it's better to love.

00:18:11.190 --> 00:18:16.560
It's better to abide by the
principles and the philosophy

00:18:16.560 --> 00:18:23.400
of nonviolence and never hate for
hate is too heavy a burden to bear.

00:18:23.400 --> 00:18:28.570
&gt;&gt; Kojo Nnamdi: A. Philip Randolph
was the head of the Brotherhood

00:18:28.570 --> 00:18:33.430
of Sleeping Car Porters, and
